A 34-year-old man was arrested in the Durban CBD after police from the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit found drugs worth R900 000 concealed in a spare tyre on Tuesday night. KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said the arrest was made after the police team received information about a person who was transporting drugs in the Durban CBD. ALSO READ | KZN man (73) hacks girlfriend and grandchildren to death with a bushknife “The suspect’s vehicle was spotted at the corner of Dr Pixley KaSeme and Russel streets. The suspect immediately sped off upon seeing the police officers. “A chase ensued, and the suspect was intercepted with the assistance of the Durban Flying Squad. “A search was conducted inside the vehicle and 2,71kgs of pure heroin and 1,420kgs of crystal meth were found. The drugs were found concealed in a spare tyre and inside the vehicle door pad,” said Gwala. She said cash to the value of R41 050 was seized from the man. The estimated street value of the recovered drugs is R900 000. Gwala said the 34-year-old man, who was charged with possession of drugs, is expected to appear at the Durban Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. ALSO READ | 20-year sentence for Pietermaritzburg woman who stabbed employer to death The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula welcomed the arrest of the alleged drug dealer. “This arrest proves that we are determined to creating a safer festive season for everyone,” he said.